WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/01 11:43:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=795.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/allencraig1/Syll4.jpg width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I want one! *cries*</span><hr size=1> Bard speed does ramp up with level.  <br><br>At the level it's obtained, spirit of wolf / spirit of cheetah are faster than selo's by a bard of the same level, but higher level bards can outrun those spells.<br><br>Ie: a level 9 shaman sow will move the guy faster than level 9 bard selo's, but come level 15 the bard will be moving faster than a sow cast by a level 15 shaman.<br><br>Bards with magic drums at high levels can hit the maximum speed cap (the speed which the game won't allow you to run faster than).<br><br>All that being said, spirit of the cheetah is pretty quick, and as mentioned above, for a warrior or a rogue it's a really nice incentive.  Jboots provide the smallest speed increase of all movement enhancing spells / songs / effects, so even for people who have them the higher level horses are a nice incentive / cash sink.<br><br>It sounds from reading the promo that there's two pricing scales, one for horse color, another for horse speed, so if you bought the fastest speed and the most common color, you could probably get it for less than 100K (if I had to guess, I'd say 70k or so).<br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaeonii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeonii</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://